Package org.wmn4j.notation

Class MeasureAttributes

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wmn4j.notation.MeasureAttributes
  • public final class MeasureAttributes
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the attributes of a measure that are often implicit in the measure, such as clef in effect, time signature, key signature and so on.

      • getClefChanges

        public java.util.List<Offset<Clef>> getClefChanges()
        Returns the clef changes specified in the attributes.

        The placement of clef changes are represented using Offset types, where the placement of the clef change is measured by an offset from the beginning of th measure. The list is sorted in ascending order of offset.

        Returns:
        the clef changes specified in the attributes

      • containsDirections

        Returns:

      • getDirections

        public java.util.List<Offset<Direction>> getDirections()
        Returns an unmodifiable view of the directions in these attributes.

        The directions are sorted in ascending order of offset duration. The offsets are measured from the beginning of the measure.

        Returns:
        an unmodifiable view of the directions in these attributes
